<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Male.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48, 49" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figures 48, 49. Brueelia kratochvili Balat, 1958, ex Motacilla flava Linnaeus, 1758 48 Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views 49 Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.32423.figures48-49" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/262213" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">48</figureCitation>
. Basal apodeme constricted at about midpoint (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 50–54" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 50 - 54. Brueelia kratochvili Balat, 1958, ex Motacilla flava Linnaeus, 1758 50 Male head, dorsal and ventral views 51 Male genitalia, dorsal view 52 Male mesosome, ventral view 53 Male paramere, dorsal view 54 Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.32423.figures50-54" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/262214" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">51</figureCitation>
). Proximal mesosome large (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 50–54" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 50 - 54. Brueelia kratochvili Balat, 1958, ex Motacilla flava Linnaeus, 1758 50 Male head, dorsal and ventral views 51 Male genitalia, dorsal view 52 Male mesosome, ventral view 53 Male paramere, dorsal view 54 Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.32423.figures50-54" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/262214" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">52</figureCitation>
), gently rounded. Mesosomal lobes broad, highly convergent distally; rugose area extensive in distal end. Gonopore semi-oval, longer than wide. Parameres broad, extended distally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 50–54" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 50 - 54. Brueelia kratochvili Balat, 1958, ex Motacilla flava Linnaeus, 1758 50 Male head, dorsal and ventral views 51 Male genitalia, dorsal view 52 Male mesosome, ventral view 53 Male paramere, dorsal view 54 Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.32423.figures50-54" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/262214" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">53</figureCitation>
); 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">pst1-2</emphasis>
as in Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 50–54" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 50 - 54. Brueelia kratochvili Balat, 1958, ex Motacilla flava Linnaeus, 1758 50 Male head, dorsal and ventral views 51 Male genitalia, dorsal view 52 Male mesosome, ventral view 53 Male paramere, dorsal view 54 Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.32423.figures50-54" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/262214" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">53</figureCitation>
. Measurements ex 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Michahelles" authorityYear="1830" class="Aves" family="Motacillidae" genus="Motacilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Motacilla flava subsp. feldegg" order="Passeriformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="flava" subSpecies="feldegg">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Motacilla flava feldegg</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">n</emphasis>
= 8): TL = 1.55-1.72; HL = 0.33-0.35; HW = 0.26-0.28; PRW = 0.18-0.19; PTW = 0.26-0.28; AW = 0.31-0.37. Measurements ex 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Aves" family="Motacillidae" genus="Motacilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Motacilla flava" order="Passeriformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Motacilla flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ssp. (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">n</emphasis>
= 7): TL = 1.58-1.74; HL = 0.32-0.35; HW = 0.25-0.28; PRW = 0.18-0.20; PTW = 0.25-0.29; AW = 0.32-0.36.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Female.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48, 49" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figures 48, 49. Brueelia kratochvili Balat, 1958, ex Motacilla flava Linnaeus, 1758 48 Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views 49 Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.32423.figures48-49" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/262213" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">49</figureCitation>
. Subgenital plate rounded rectangular, with narrow connection to cross-piece (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 50–54" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 50 - 54. Brueelia kratochvili Balat, 1958, ex Motacilla flava Linnaeus, 1758 50 Male head, dorsal and ventral views 51 Male genitalia, dorsal view 52 Male mesosome, ventral view 53 Male paramere, dorsal view 54 Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.32423.figures50-54" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/262214" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">54</figureCitation>
). Vulval margin gently rounded, with 3 or 4 short, slender 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">vms</emphasis>
and 3-5 short, thorn-like 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">vss</emphasis>
on each side; 5 or 6 short, slender 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">vos</emphasis>
on each side of subgenital plate; distal 1 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">vos</emphasis>
median to 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">vss.</emphasis>
Measurements ex 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Michahelles" authorityYear="1830" class="Aves" family="Motacillidae" genus="Motacilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Motacilla flava subsp. feldegg" order="Passeriformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="flava" subSpecies="feldegg">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Motacilla flava feldegg</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">n</emphasis>
= 10): TL = 1.88-2.06 (2.00); HL = 0.35-0.39 (0.37); HW = 0.29-0.32 (0.31); PRW = 0.20-0.22 (0.21); PTW = 0.28-0.32 (0.30); AW = 0.39-0.44 (0.42). Measurements ex 
